  "text": "Envoy implements comprehensive HTTP request header injection validation through multiple layers of defense:\n\n## Header Validation Logic\n\nThe primary header validation functions are located in `source/common/http/header_utility.cc` and `source/common/http/header_utility.h`. The core validation functions include:\n\n1. **HeaderUtility::headerNameIsValid()** - Validates header names using RFC 9110 character tables defined in `source/common/http/character_set_validation.h`. The function checks that each character in the header name is in the valid tchar set: \"!#$%&'*+-.0-9A-Za-z^_`|~\"\n\n2. **HeaderUtility::headerValueIsValid()** - Uses the quiche http2 adapter's HeaderValidator to validate header values according to RFC 7230, allowing VCHAR and obs-text characters but rejecting control characters that could enable header injection attacks (carriage return, line feed, null bytes).\n\n3. **HeaderUtility::isRemovableHeader()** - Enforces that pseudo-headers (starting with ':') and the 'Host' header cannot be removed, preventing request smuggling via header removal.\n\n## Universal Header Validator (UHV) Extension\n\nEnvoy v1.31+ implements a more comprehensive validation system through the Universal Header Validator extension in `source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/`. This includes:\n\n1. **Character Tables** (`character_tables.h`) - Defines RFC-compliant character tables for:\n   - Method headers (RFC 9110)\n   - Path headers (RFC 3986)\n   - Generic header names/values\n\n2. **HTTP/1 Header Validator** (`http1_header_validator.cc/h`) - Implements HTTP/1-specific validation:\n   - Validates Transfer-Encoding and Content-Length headers to prevent attacks\n   - Validates method, scheme, authority, and path headers\n   - Detects underscore characters in header names (security measure for legacy systems)\n\n3. **HTTP/2 Header Validator** (`http2_header_validator.cc/h`) - HTTP/2-specific validation including pseudo-header validation and content-length handling.\n\n## Forbidden Header List and Internal Header Stripping\n\nInternal header stripping is implemented in `source/common/http/conn_manager_utility.cc` in the `ConnectionManagerUtility::cleanInternalHeaders()` function. This function removes Envoy-internal headers from edge requests to prevent client injection:\n\n- **Edge Request Sanitization** - Removes headers that clients cannot inject:\n  - x-envoy-decorator-operation\n  - x-envoy-downstream-service-cluster\n  - x-envoy-downstream-service-node\n  - x-envoy-original-path\n  - x-envoy-original-host\n\n- **External Request Sanitization** - Removes headers from all external requests:\n  - x-envoy-retriable-status-codes\n  - x-envoy-retriable-header-names\n  - x-envoy-retry-on\n  - x-envoy-retry-grpc-on\n  - x-envoy-max-retries\n  - x-envoy-upstream-request-timeout-ms\n  - x-envoy-force-trace\n  - x-envoy-ip-tags\n  - x-envoy-original-url\n  - x-envoy-hedge-on-per-try-timeout\n  - Custom internal-only headers from configuration\n\n## HTTP/1 Codec-Level Validation\n\nThe HTTP/1 codec in `source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc` implements additional validation:\n\n1. **Underscore Handling** - The `ServerConnectionImpl::checkHeaderNameForUnderscores()` function enforces the configured action (ALLOW, DROP_HEADER, or REJECT_REQUEST) for headers containing underscores.\n\n2. **Invalid Character Detection** - Uses `HeaderUtility::headerValueIsValid()` to reject headers with invalid characters during parsing.\n\n3. **Balsa Parser** - The underlying balsa_parser.cc uses character validation tables conforming to RFC 9110, validating all header names match the tchar set.\n\n## Error Reporting\n\nValidation failures are reported with specific error codes defined in `envoy/http/header_validator_errors.h`:\n- uhv.invalid_name_characters\n- uhv.invalid_value_characters\n- uhv.invalid_underscore\n- http1.invalid_characters\n\nThis multi-layered approach prevents HTTP request header injection attacks by validating header syntax at multiple stages: HTTP codec parsing, connection manager cleanup, and application-level header validators."
